what_failed: Regression (0.92x): Created three filtered dimension CTEs (date, item, address) to materialize small filtered subsets once, then reused them across all three sales channel CTEs. This eliminates repeated scanning and filtering of the same dimension tables and allows efficient hash joins with the large fact tables.
why_it_failed: Created year-specific CTEs (store_sales_1999, store_sales_2000, etc.) but KEPT the original year_total union CTE alongside them. The optimizer materializes both the split versions and the original union, resulting in redundant computation. Projection cardinality estimates show 10^16x errors from the confused CTE graph.
